NAME
    Permute::Unnamed - Permute multiple-valued lists

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.001 of Permute::Unnamed (from Perl
    distribution Permute-Unnamed), released on 2026-02-21.

SYNOPSIS
     use Permute::Unnamed;

     my @p = permute_unnamed([ 0, 1 ], [qw(foo bar baz)]);
     # => (
     #   [0, "foo"],
     #   [0, "bar"],
     #   [0, "baz"],
     #   [1, "foo"],
     #   [1, "bar"],
     #   [1, "baz"],
     # )

DESCRIPTION
    This module is like Set::CrossProduct, except that it allows only a
    single argument.

FUNCTIONS
  permute_unnamed(@list) => @list | $arrayref
HOMEPAGE
    Please visit the project's homepage at
    <https://metacpan.org/release/Permute-Unnamed>.

